as is Ani DiFranco you can't hide behind social graces so don't try to be all touchy feely cuz you lie in my face of all places but i've got no problem with that really what bugs me is that you believe what you're saying what bothers me is that you don't know how you feel what scares me is that while you're telling me stories you actually believe that they are real and i've got no illusions about you and guess what? i never did and when i said when i said i'll take it i meant, i meant as is just give up and admit you're an asshole you would be in some good company i think you'd find that your friends would forgive you or maybe i am just speaking for me cuz when i look around i think this, this is good enough and i try to laugh at whatever life brings cuz when i look down i just miss all the good stuff when i look up i just trip over things and i've got no illusions about you...

imperfectly- Ani DiFranco i'm okay if you get me at a good angle and you're okay in the right sort of light and we don't look like pages from a magazine but that's all right that's all right i crashed your pickup truck and then i had to drive it back home i was crying i was so scared of what you would do of what you would say but you just started laughing so i started laughing along saying, it looks a little rough but it runs okay it looks a little rough but it runs good anyway we get a little further from perfection each year on the road i guess that's what they call character i guess that's just the way it goes better to be dusty than polished like some store window mannequin why don't you touch me where i'm rusty let me stain your hands when you're pretty as a picture they pound down your door but i've been offered love in two dimensions before and i know that it's not all it's made out to be let's show them how it's done let's do it all imperfectly

well yesterday I found out Eddie and Paul got in a car accident on Dalton road. Eddie was very very drunk and Paul did not want him to be alone in case he did get into one. We went and saw him yesterday in the hospital. But Eddie got thrown through the windshield and now he can not move the lower half of his body. I really hope that everything will be okay and he is not paralyzed. that is horrible.

I was informed last night I may be the new singer of a local punk band called Black Listed. They kicked out one of their guitarists and now the singer wants to go full time guitar. I hope this happens because they have already established a name for themselves. but it will be hard to live up to people's expectations for us because they are an awesome band. I'll probably fuck it up for them. anyway the band as of now is... Andy- Bass (Mike's little brother who I am convinced is homosexual despite his mohawk and "punk" appearance) Chris- Guitar and vocals (Kristi's cousin....I really do not know him at all but he seems like a cool kid...) AJ- Drums (I tried to beat this kid's ass a few months ago but Tina stopped me hahaha) My friend Derek was the one who got kicked out. hope there will be no hard feelings between us. and also Monday I went to the Manchester mall with Tina and Ariel. When we were driving down Ariel's road Tina lost control of the car and we almost slammed into a wall but Tina managed to drive into a snow bank instead. We all thought the car was going to flip. Tina prayed and spoke in tongues for about half an hour after that. We got lost in Manchester. Then we got to the mall a lot later then was expected and I met up with Jake. I wanted to tell him about Mike but I did not have the heart. We left at around 7:30ish....We got lost again for awhile and Drove down a one way street the wrong way thanks to Ariel who can not say left or right instead it is that way! but that is okay. Then as we were driving through the Franconia notch (The worst place to drive during the winter) and did the same thing but this time is was a million times scarier because it was on the highway and we went in a complete circle because Tina did not want to hit the guardrail thing. Surprisingly Her car is hardly damaged at all Her door is a little fucked up and her license plate is bent but that is because she hit the pole that be were parked behind at the mall. forward reverse it is all the same damn thing...haha but Tina is a really good driver nevertheless. heh and a bunch more shit is going on that is will write about later because my class is going to end any minute. Jesus this is the most I have wrote in a journal EVER! BYE!
